                                <h3 id="faq">Quick FAQ.</h3>
                                <div style="margin-left:10px;">
                                    <b>Bitcoin:</b>
                                    <div style="margin-left:10px;">
                                        <p><b>What happens when I lose the private key of a 2-2 key as a vendor?</b></p>
                                        <p>You will not be able to retrieve the coins in escrow.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens if the staff lose control of the Bitcoin?</b></p>
                                        <p>The coins are held in a timelock and will be released to the buyer after 30 days.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens when a vendor gets banned and I have a 2-2 transaction with him?</b>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>The refund process will take much longer as they have to be paid from our own
                                            pockets.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens when I lose the private keys to a 2-3 key as a vendor?</b></p>
                                        <p>If the customer has his key he can contact support and we will finalize the order for
                                            you.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens if I as customer lose my multi-sig key?</b></p>
                                        <p>If the vendor is inactive on this market you will need to wait for him to return in
                                            case of a refund.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens if I lose access to my Bitcoin return address in my settings?</b></p>
                                        <p>If we have not issued a refund you can always change it. If we have issued one the
                                            coins are lost.</p>
                                        <p><b>Do I need to sign a transaction as a customer?</b></p>
                                        <p>No, this is done automatically. Only the one time setup and possible signing for a
                                            dispute.</p>
                                        <p><b>Who has access to the coins in Escrow?</b></p>
                                        <p>Nobody, the address has no private key. The coins are suspended by the two or three
                                            keys until a transaction is signed.</p>
                                        <p><b>Is there any information I need to save from a multi-sig order?</b></p>
                                        <p>As customer and vendor it is handy to copy the "Multisig Redeemscript" so orders can
                                            be finalized without the market.</p>
                                        <p>As a vendor download the locktime transactions which can be used to finalize the
                                            order after 90 days by yourself.</p>
                                        <p><b>Can I change or remove my multi-sig address while orders is in transit?</b></p>
                                        <p>Yes, but don't lose track off the assigned addresses.</p>
                                        <p><b>Can I change multi-sig keys on a shipped or accepted order transaction?</b></p>
                                        <p>No, if a key has been assigned to a transaction it is not possible to change
                                            this.</p>
                                        <p><b>Can I change my Bitcoin return (refund) address while my order is in transit /
                                                dispute?</b></p>
                                        <p>For customers, yes. For vendors, yes but the address will be assigned to current
                                            Locktime transactions.</p>
                                        <br>
                                    </div>
                                    <b>Monero/Zcash:</b>
                                    <div style="margin-left:10px;">
                                        <p><b>What happens when I lose the private key of the Monero/Zcash address as a
                                                vendor?</b></p>
                                        <p>Change the address in your Currency tab. Any new coins will be deposited in the new
                                            address.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens when a vendor gets banned and I have a transaction with him?</b></p>
                                        <p>It will be refunded.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens if I as customer lose my private key?</b></p>
                                        <p>Change the address in your Currency tab. Any new refunds will be deposited in the new
                                            address.</p>
                                        <p><b>What happens if I lose access to my Monero return address in my settings?</b></p>
                                        <p>If we have not issued a refund you can always change it. If we have issued one the
                                            coins are lost.</p>
                                        <p><b>Who has access to the coins in Escrow?</b></p>
                                        <p>The marketplace.</p>
                                        <p><b>Can I change or remove my address while orders is in transit?</b></p>
                                        <p>Yes, but don't lose track off the assigned addresses.</p>
                                        <p><b>Can I change Monero/Zcash address on a shipped or accepted order transaction?</b>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>Yes, change the address in your settings.</p>
                                        <p><b>Can I change my Monero return (refund) address while my order is in transit /
                                                dispute?</b></p>
                                        <p>For customers, yes. For vendors, yes.</p>
                                    </div>
